<TITLE> Bush says strong verification needed on N Korea </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 SEOUL Wed Aug 6, (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - US President George W Bush on Wednesday said strong verification of North Korea's nuclear weapons programme was necessary to address concerns about it. "I'm concerned about its unranium enrichment activities as well as its nuclear testing and proliferation, its ballistic missile programmes," Bush said during a news conference after meeting with South Korean President Lee Myung-bak. "The best way to approach and answer those concerns is for there to be strong verification measures," Bush said
